    "Name": "Caesar",
    "Details": "The -3R was built to do as much damage to an enemy at as great a stand-off range as possible. The 'Mech therefore carries primarily long-ranged armament. To save weight it also uses an 280-rated XL engine and sixteen double heat sinks, allowing the 'Mech to carry as many weapons and as much armor as possible. The primary long-ranged weapon on the Caesar is a Gauss rifle, supplied with two tons of reloads. This is backed up at long ranges by an ER PPC, which can do two-thirds of the damage of the Gauss rifle but is not dependent on limited ammunition. For close-range engagements, the Caesar carries four Medium Pulse Lasers, allowing it to put up a crippling defense against any enemies that can get close to the 'Mech.\n\n<b><color=#e62e00>Quirk: Hyper-Extending Actuators</color></b>\n\n<b><color=#e62e00>Drop Cost Multiplier: 1.1</color></b>",
